  "text": "The Kafka consumer's heartbeat session timeout is defined in CommonClientConfigs.java via the SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG constant ('session.timeout.ms'). This configuration value is used by GroupRebalanceConfig.java to set the sessionTimeoutMs field, which is passed to the Heartbeat class during initialization. The Heartbeat.java class uses this timeout value to create a sessionTimer and provides the sessionTimeoutExpired(long now) method to check if the timeout has expired. During the consumer polling loop, the AbstractCoordinator.java class runs a background HeartbeatThread that periodically checks if the session timeout has expired by calling heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now) at line 1513. When the session timeout is detected as expired without receiving a successful heartbeat response, the thread calls markCoordinatorUnknown('session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response') at line 1516. This triggers the removal of the consumer from the group, resulting in the consumer losing its membership and causing the reported 'Heartbeat session timed out' behavior where the consumer drops from the group."
}

